{
  "name": "IBM MQ OTel - Dashboard",
  "description": "Monitor IBM MQ infrastructure instrumented via the OpenTelemetry collector (NRDot scraping the IBM MQ Prometheus exporter). Tracks queue manager health, queue depth and throughput, channel performance, and filesystem utilization.",
  "pages": [
    {
      "name": "Queue Managers",
      "description": null,
      "widgets": [
        {
          "title": "",
          "layout": {
            "column": 1,
            "row": 1,
            "width": 2,
            "height": 3
          },
          "linkedEntityGuids": null,
          "visualization": {
            "id": "viz.markdown"
          },
          "rawConfiguration": {
            "text": " ![IBM-MQ logo](https://github.com/newrelic/newrelic-quickstarts/blob/main/quickstarts/ibmmq-otel/logo.png?raw=true)\n\n\n\n To scope page to a single cluster, filter by `qmgr=<queueManagerName>`\n \n Dashboard gives an overview of your Queue Managers, their queues, and their channels — sourced from an OpenTelemetry collector (NRDot) scraping the IBM MQ Prometheus exporter.\n\n [IBM MQ OTel instrumentation guide](https://docs.newrelic.com/docs/opentelemetry/get-started/collector-infrastructure-monitoring/opentelemetry-collector-infra-hosts/)\n"
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "",
          "layout": {
            "column": 3,
            "row": 1,
            "width": 2,
            "height": 3
          },
          "linkedEntityGuids": null,
          "visualization": {
            "id": "viz.billboard"
          },
          "rawConfiguration": {
            "dataFormatters": [],
            "nrqlQueries": [
              {
                "accountId": 0,
                "query": "SELECT latest(ibmmq_qmgr_connection_count) AS 'Connections' FROM Metric WHERE instrumentation.provider = 'opentelemetry' COMPARE WITH 1 hour ago"
              }
            ],
            "thresholds": []
          }
        },
        {
          "title": "Connections",
          "layout": {
            "column": 5,
            "row": 1,
            "width": 4,
            "height": 3
